  "texts": [
    "Anthropomorphism, or assigning human-like characteristics to non-human entities, is commonplace in people's interactions with technology (Vasconcelos et al., 2023).",
    "However, anthropomorphizing language can suggest undue accountability and agency in technologies like artificial intelligence (AI) and language models (LMs).",
    "Projecting human qualities onto these tools facilitates misinformation about their true capabilities, over-reliance on technology, and corporate avoidance of responsibility (Watson, 2019; Shneiderman, 2020 Shneiderman,, 2022;; Shanahan, 2022; Hunter, 2023).",
    "Such metaphors are especially consequential in public discourse",
    "We propose a network that uses self-supervised learning to identify important features."
  ],
